<article id="node-1961" class="node node-article view-mode-full clearfix desktop-100" about="/departments/inspectional-services/zoning-board-appeal" typeof="sioc:Item foaf:Document">
      <div class="brc-lu">
      Last updated: 
  <span class="date-display-single" property="dc:date" datatype="xsd:dateTime" content="2019-09-13T14:45:00-04:00">9/13/19</span>    </div>
    <div class="department-info-wrapper desktop-100">
    <div class="column mobile-100 desktop-66-left">
      <h1 class="title">Zoning Board of Appeal</h1>
              <div class="intro-text supporting-text squiggle-border-bottom">
  <p><span>We inspect and review buildings for zoning compliance. The board regulates the rules behind what you can build and where you can build in Boston.</span></p>
</div>
            <div class="sub-nav-trigger drawer-trigger">
        <div class="sub-nav-chevron">
                  </div>
        Page Sections
      </div>
      <nav class="topic-nav topic-nav__left">
        <ul></ul>
        <a name="section-nav"></a>
      </nav>
      <div class="body">
        <div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><div class="field-items"><div class="field-item even" property="content:encoded"><p>City officials created the <a href="http://www.bostonredevelopmentauthority.org/zoning" rel="nofollow">Boston Zoning Code</a> in 1964. There are now 14 neighborhood codes and 18 codes for downtown Boston and the waterfront. Learn more about zoning and how it might affect your project at the next <a href="/departments/inspectional-services/how-zoning-board-appeal-works#nav1206642751">Zoning Clinic</a>. You can also <a href="http://maps.bostonredevelopmentauthority.org/zoningviewer/" rel="nofollow">find the zoning for addresses in the City</a>.</p>
<p><a class="button" href="https://library.municode.com/ma/boston/codes/redevelopment_authority" rel="nofollow">Zoning codes in Boston</a>.</p>
</div></div></div>      </div>
    </div>
